<span class="header1">MILITARY</span>
<p>There are many technical jobs in the military that offer excitement and challenge. You may find one of these to be to your liking.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Air Traffic Controller</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/EF/43161.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Air Traffic Controller" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>An air traffic controller uses radar and computer equipment to track aircraft while they are in the air. As an air traffic controller, you would talk to the aircraft pilots at take-off and landing. You would make sure that only one aircraft was on the runway at a time. You would also make sure that they stayed a certain distance from each other while they were in the air.  This is an important job.  Many people's safety depends on the controller.  You can also do this job as a civilian.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>To be an air traffic controller, you must receive special training.  An air traffic controller for the military receives training on a military base. The Federal Aviation Agency trains civilian controllers.  A civil service exam must be passed.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary you receive in the military is based on your rank, years of service, and job.  The yearly salary for a civilian controller ranges from $55,000 to $136,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Air Crew Member</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/EF/M041.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Air Crew Member" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a member of an aircrew, you would do one of several different jobs on a military aircraft. You might run the communication and radar equipment, the gunnery systems or other machinery aboard. You might also operate and maintain the in-flight refueling system. This can be a very stressful job.  It puts your physical stamina to the test.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>All of the jobs on an aircraft require specialized training. The majority of training is done by the military. A high school diploma is acceptable, but a college degree is preferred.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary you receive in the military is based on your rank, years of service, and job.</blockquote>

