<span class="header1">OUTDOOR OPERATIONS</span>
<p>The occupations found in this category are for people who like working with equipment, tools, and technology. If this sounds like you, you might want to work in this field.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Cartographer</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A cartographer creates maps.  As a cartographer, you would use information from land surveyors, photographs, and satellites. You would spend much of your time on a computer creating maps from this information.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Most cartographers have at least a degree in engineering or science.  Some employees become cartographers by working as a cartographic technician first. This job does not require a degree.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The average yearly salary is $46,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Truck Driver</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/EF/1168.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Truck Driver" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a truck driver, you would take loads of goods and produce across the country to be sold. You would be responsible for whatever you were hauling in your truck until you delivered it to its drop-off.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Most companies prefer their truck drivers to have high school diplomas. There are schools that provide training for truck drivers. Each state has strict regulations on the trucking industry.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>Most of the time, a truck driver is paid by the hour or by the mile. The yearly salary ranges from $20,000 to $49,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Heavy Equipment Operator</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/EF/1396.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Heavy Equipment Operator" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Equipment operators use heavy machinery such as cranes and bulldozers to move dirt, wood, or other materials used in construction.  If you were an equipment operator, you might work at road paving sites.  You might also work at industrial and construction sites.  This equipment can be dangerous.  Safety practices are a big concern.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a high school diploma for this job.  You are more likely to get a job operating expensive equipment if you have taken courses at a vocational school.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>A general salary range for this job is $19,000 to $53,000 per year.</blockquote>

